-- South African Equities: AngloGold, Harmony Gold, BHP Billiton
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-12-30T15:46:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/south-african-equities-bhp-capital-shopping-impala-platinum.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  advanced for the second day, adding 86.64, or 0.3
percent, to 32,210.04 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  The following are among the most active stocks in the South
African market today.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd.  (ANG SJ), Africa’s biggest gold
producer, fell 2.68 rand, or 0.8 percent, to 327.72 rand. Gold
for immediate delivery declined as much as 0.5 percent to
$1,405.25 an ounce.  Harmony Gold Mining Co.  (HAR SJ) dropped 35
cents, or 0.4 percent, to 83.05 rand, while DRDGold Ltd. (DRD
SJ) fell 3 cents, or 0.9 percent, to 3.23 rand.  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ), the world’s largest mining
company, advanced 1.50 rand, or 0.6 percent, to 269.75 rand.
Copper surged to records in London and New York on speculation
the global recovery is gaining pace and as investor concerns
about tightening in China eased after manufacturing growth in
the world’s largest metals user slowed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Franz Wild  in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
